==English==

===Etymology===
Origin of the word is subject to much debate but most pundits credit it to ex-player and now manager of [[Wikipedia:Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace F.C.]] [[Wikipedia:Iain Dowie|Iain Dowie]] in reference to his team's unexpected return to winning form. The word was popularised on topical football show [[Wikipedia:Soccer AM|Soccer AM]] on Sky Sports in the United Kingdom, where during the season 2004/05 it has become the object of a cult following.

===Noun===
'''bouncebackability'''

#The ability of a person or team to [[bounce back]], that is, to return to good form after a period of not performing well.
#: ''By passing the test, after last years abysmal failure, he exhibited great '''bouncebackability'''.''
#The ability to recover from a past relationship.

